  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Time City Infrastructure and Housing Limited Lucknow  versus The State of U.P. & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_8_730_739','2025INSC966'); ><font size='4'> <strong>TIME CITY INFRASTRUCTURE AND HOUSING LIMITED LUCKNOW <span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF U.P. & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 730</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 966</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006132025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The High Court set aside the order passed by the Civil Judge (Senior Division) granting ex parte injunction as prayed for by the petitioner &ndash; herein in Civil Suit No.447/2025. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 &ndash; Proviso Trial Court granted ex parte injunction in favour of petitioner- herein (original plaintiff) &ndash; Respondents herein (original defendants) invoked supervisory jurisdiction of the High Court u/Art.227 &ndash; The High Court held, inter-alia, that the trial Court has not considered the suit<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 11-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 21747/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_8_730_739','2025INSC966','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-s